<i>DALE: This is no game, Ray.</i>
<i>This is real.</i>

26
00:06:10,721 --> 00:06:12,954
<i>Like I told you, man,</i>
<i>this is old-school espionage.</i>

27
00:06:13,060 --> 00:06:15,690
<i>Moscow rules. Street spies.</i>

28
00:06:15,766 --> 00:06:17,564
<i>RAY: How far behind me?</i>

29
00:06:17,636 --> 00:06:20,538
<i>DALE: He's about three meters back.</i>
<i>He must have picked us up downtown.</i>

30
00:06:20,608 --> 00:06:22,076
<i>RAY: And you know this guy?</i>

31
00:06:22,144 --> 00:06:25,548
<i>DALE: I've seen him around.</i>
<i>He's definitely Burkett & Randle.</i>

32
00:06:25,617 --> 00:06:30,149
<i>I keep telling you, man. These people</i>
<i>take soap and shaving cream very seriously.</i>

33
00:06:30,261 --> 00:06:32,822
So I guess that means we're going to plan B.

34
00:06:32,932 --> 00:06:34,298
<i>DALE: Let's do it.</i>

35
00:06:34,401 --> 00:06:37,601
- What's he wearing?
<i>- Navy turtleneck, gray jacket.</i>

36
00:06:45,255 --> 00:06:48,159
That was sweet, man.
It's all good. It's all good.

37
00:06:48,262 --> 00:06:50,663
There's no way this guy is working solo,
so if we want to bust you out,

38
00:06:50,766 --> 00:06:54,137
we're gonna have to make a little noise
up here at the corner.

39
00:06:58,148 --> 00:07:00,778
<i>DALE: You wanna box him out of here</i>
<i>or leapfrog? What do you wanna do?</i>

40
00:07:00,853 --> 00:07:02,846
I still think you're messing with me.

41
00:07:02,958 --> 00:07:05,189
Call it, Ray. Box or leapfrog?

42
00:07:05,661 --> 00:07:08,690
Or maybe you just want to find out
if I'm worth the money.

43
00:07:08,802 --> 00:07:11,797
<i>- DALE: Come on, man.</i>
- Leapfrog.

44
00:07:17,351 --> 00:07:18,512
Jesus!

45
00:07:20,557 --> 00:07:23,189
Watch where you go. It's New York, okay?

46
00:07:23,297 --> 00:07:24,788
Let me help.

47
00:07:25,867 --> 00:07:27,360
Open the eyes!

48
00:08:52,671 --> 00:08:55,198
- Hey, you there?
<i>- DALE: What are you doing?</i>

49
00:08:55,711 --> 00:08:56,735
Problem.

50
00:08:58,582 --> 00:09:02,580
<i>- DALE: I thought you were in position.</i>
- I am. I was.

51
00:09:02,691 --> 00:09:04,182
<i>DALE: We're two minutes away.</i>

52
00:09:04,259 --> 00:09:06,754
- We're blown.
<i>- What are you talking about?</i>

53
00:09:06,865 --> 00:09:07,993
Reschedule the meet.

54
00:09:08,067 --> 00:09:10,061
No. No can do.

55
00:09:10,773 --> 00:09:12,402
We're blown. Just walk away.

56
00:09:12,509 --> 00:09:15,913
Listen to me. I know what it's like.
New guy on the team, big game,

57
00:09:16,015 --> 00:09:18,384
<i>you wanna make a good impression.</i>

58
00:09:20,191 --> 00:09:21,557
Hello? Ray?

59
00:10:36,506 --> 00:10:37,907
Remember me?

60
00:10:41,716 --> 00:10:44,415
- Sure. Of course. We...
- Long time, huh?

61
00:10:45,457 --> 00:10:47,690
- Yes!
- Gotcha.

62
00:10:49,767 --> 00:10:52,293
- I'm sorry, I just...
- Just what?

63
00:10:52,404 --> 00:10:53,429
I'm drawing a blank.

64
00:10:53,539 --> 00:10:55,202
- Nice try.
- Excuse me?

65
00:10:55,277 --> 00:10:58,215
A little professional courtesy
would make this a lot less awkward.

66
00:10:58,283 --> 00:11:00,947
- How do I know you?
- How do you know me?

67
00:11:01,923 --> 00:11:05,590
Wow! That's tough.
That's a strong play.

68
00:11:06,298 --> 00:11:09,566
Believe me, I've spent a lot of time thinking
what this would be like,

69
00:11:09,639 --> 00:11:11,972
where we'd be, what I'd say, what you'd say.

70
00:11:12,076 --> 00:11:14,240
- But I never thought that you'd...
- I'm terribly sorry.

71
00:11:14,313 --> 00:11:15,782
You really want to go this way?

72
00:11:15,850 --> 00:11:17,479
You clearly have me confused
with someone else.

73
00:11:17,586 --> 00:11:18,679
I don't know.

74
00:11:18,788 --> 00:11:21,317
I mean, I'm not great on names.
I should be. I try.

75
00:11:21,427 --> 00:11:24,193
Faces, I'm definitely better.
Faces, I'm like a B, B minus.

76
00:11:24,299 --> 00:11:27,466
Where I'm good, where I really excel,
people I've slept with.

77
00:11:27,539 --> 00:11:30,203
That's been a traditional area of strength
for me.

78
00:11:30,312 --> 00:11:33,341
Look, seriously,
I don't know who you think I am, but...

79
00:11:33,451 --> 00:11:35,010
You charm me, you seduce me,
you screw me,

80
00:11:35,121 --> 00:11:37,557
then you drug me
and ransack my hotel room.

81
00:11:37,659 --> 00:11:40,894
And how sick is this? You know, the last
thing I remember before I passed out

82
00:11:40,999 --> 00:11:42,969
was how much I liked you.

83
00:11:43,471 --> 00:11:46,466
All right. You don't look crazy,

84
00:11:46,543 --> 00:11:48,307
which is the only reason
why I'm not screaming

85
00:11:48,379 --> 00:11:52,684
- for a security guard right now, but...
- I can't believe you're going this way.

86
00:11:52,755 --> 00:11:56,695
Wait. Is this a joke?
Is that what it is?

87
00:11:56,931 --> 00:11:59,595
Do you have any idea how far my ass
was hanging out because of you?

88
00:11:59,702 --> 00:12:01,433
Did I win something?

89
00:12:02,942 --> 00:12:05,105
I woke up the next morning,
I went back to the consul.

90
00:12:05,212 --> 00:12:07,878
I practically crawled over glass
to get a copy of the guest list.

91
00:12:07,951 --> 00:12:09,716
I spent the next 24 hours trying to figure out

92
00:12:09,822 --> 00:12:13,659
if you were working for Mossad,
the Syrians or the Russians.

93
00:12:13,730 --> 00:12:16,725
- And which was it?
- Still working for the CIA?

94
00:12:17,537 --> 00:12:19,734
Okay, I think we're done now.

95
00:12:20,176 --> 00:12:24,013
American Consulate, Dubai,
you and me, Fourth of July, 2003.

96
00:12:24,082 --> 00:12:25,210
Find someone else to bother.

97
00:12:25,286 --> 00:12:27,448
- Red, white and blue margaritas.
- Stay away from me.

98
00:12:27,557 --> 00:12:30,859
I had a knee brace, you had toe rings.
First toe ring I ever saw, by the way.

99
00:12:30,929 --> 00:12:32,192
You follow me, I'll scream.

100
00:12:32,265 --> 00:12:35,260
I took vacation time to find you! Five years.

101
00:12:35,371 --> 00:12:36,738
And every time I walked into an evaluation...

102
00:12:36,808 --> 00:12:38,710
- I'm warning you for the last time.
...I was waiting for them

103
00:12:38,778 --> 00:12:39,975
to throw your picture on the screen and say,

104
00:12:40,081 --> 00:12:42,109
"So, Ray, anything you care to tell us
about Dubai?"

105
00:12:42,219 --> 00:12:45,282
- You are harassing me!
- So who the hell are you?

106
00:12:48,297 --> 00:12:51,326
Oh, no. You?

107
00:12:56,145 --> 00:12:59,140
- You're the drop.
- You're my contact?

108
00:13:03,860 --> 00:13:05,990
You're acting like
I owe you an apology.

109
00:13:06,097 --> 00:13:07,533
Knock yourself out.

110
00:13:07,634 --> 00:13:10,298
You were an assignment. You're a big boy.
You knew what you were doing.

111
00:13:10,373 --> 00:13:11,932
I can see it's really been eating at you.

112
00:13:12,009 --> 00:13:15,972
An Ml6 case officer takes a strange girl
from an embassy party

113
00:13:16,052 --> 00:13:18,818
back to his hotel room
where he has an unsecured briefcase

114
00:13:18,890 --> 00:13:21,384
- full of Egyptian Air Defense codes.
- Did they tell you to sleep with me?

115
00:13:21,495 --> 00:13:24,227
I needed the codes. I thought the less time
I spent with you, the better.

116
00:13:24,335 --> 00:13:27,134
- Oh, Jesus.
- How did you get on this project?

117
00:13:27,206 --> 00:13:29,541
- And you're the mole.
- And who the hell hired you anyway?

118
00:13:29,644 --> 00:13:31,409
- I can't believe it.
- How did you get this job?

119
00:13:31,514 --> 00:13:33,346
I got news for you, okay? The day I left Ml6,

120
00:13:33,418 --> 00:13:36,014
I had 15 major companies
begging for my services.

121
00:13:36,091 --> 00:13:38,390
Well, I guess you picked wrong.
But you must be used to that.

122
00:13:38,495 --> 00:13:41,934
- You know, I've got a meeting in 12 minutes.
- Where's the drop? Hand it over.

123
00:13:42,036 --> 00:13:45,337
- Forget it. I'm not working with you.
- Excuse me?

124
00:13:45,408 --> 00:13:48,072
You think I'm gonna let you
be my contact officer?

125
00:13:48,179 --> 00:13:50,616
- This is way over your head.
- Over my head?

126
00:13:50,719 --> 00:13:53,019
Lady, I worked Yemen, Athens and Cairo.

127
00:13:53,090 --> 00:13:55,457
I've been promoted and decorated
every place I served.

128
00:13:55,562 --> 00:13:57,029
Tell Duke to send someone else.

129
00:13:57,097 --> 00:13:59,466
Listen. I'm sure you know your way
around a shoe store,

130
00:13:59,568 --> 00:14:01,129
but I did 12 years in the field.

131
00:14:01,240 --> 00:14:02,971
And how long have you been working
for Equikrom?

132
00:14:03,076 --> 00:14:04,942
- Long enough.
- How long?

133
00:14:06,616 --> 00:14:08,051
Three weeks.

134
00:14:09,589 --> 00:14:13,083
Three whole weeks? Like every day?

135
00:14:14,331 --> 00:14:17,394
Well, I've spent the last 14 months
undercover inside Burkett & Randle.

136
00:14:17,471 --> 00:14:21,308
I'm an Assistant Director
of Counterintelligence. I am all the way in.

137
00:14:21,412 --> 00:14:25,078
So let's get this straight.
I'm the asset here. You're a delivery boy.

138
00:14:25,153 --> 00:14:27,145
And the only thing I'm gonna give you
is a message.

139
00:14:27,256 --> 00:14:30,251
Tell Duke I don't ever wanna see you again.

140
00:14:30,998 --> 00:14:34,437
I run field agents for a living.
There's only two ways to do it.

141
00:14:34,504 --> 00:14:35,529
Either you bring them flowers

142
00:14:35,639 --> 00:14:37,701
or you hang them by their heels
out of the window.

143
00:14:37,811 --> 00:14:41,113
Now, maybe you're so used to having
your legs in the air you don't realize it,

144
00:14:41,183 --> 00:14:43,779
but you're upside down, sister.

145
00:14:43,855 --> 00:14:45,120
I own you.

146
00:14:45,192 --> 00:14:50,293
- You've 10 seconds to get your hand off me.
- Or what? You won't be my friend anymore?

147
00:14:50,735 --> 00:14:54,334
I like this gig.
I like the money. I like the hours.

148
00:14:54,411 --> 00:14:56,711
So I'm not going anywhere,
and you're gonna get over it

149
00:14:56,815 --> 00:14:59,513
because if you ever mention again
that you don't wanna work with me

150
00:14:59,586 --> 00:15:03,150
or that we've met before or that you think
someone else might do a better job,

151
00:15:03,226 --> 00:15:05,924
if I get replaced for any reason at all,

152
00:15:06,033 --> 00:15:08,264
I'm gonna call those suckers
over at Burkett & Randle

153
00:15:08,370 --> 00:15:12,937
and tell them they have an Equikrom spy
in the heart of their security team.

154
00:15:14,450 --> 00:15:18,618
Be a shame to let the last 14 months
go down the drain, wouldn't it?

155
00:15:22,130 --> 00:15:24,067
So where's my package?

156
00:15:30,746 --> 00:15:33,548
Tell Duke this is the one
he's been waiting for.

157
00:15:33,620 --> 00:15:38,152
- You screw this up, I'll ruin your life.
- I thought you tried that already.

158
00:15:43,105 --> 00:15:46,168
You wanna take one last shot
at that apology?

159
00:16:11,826 --> 00:16:13,386
Okay. Thank you.

160
00:16:33,769 --> 00:16:36,900
What'd she say exactly?
I mean, her exact words.

161
00:16:37,244 --> 00:16:41,014
She said, " Tell Duke
this is the one he's been waiting for."

162
00:16:45,559 --> 00:16:47,894
Do you wanna do it?
- Go ahead.

163
00:16:50,102 --> 00:16:53,075
Easy. Just...
Just, you know, pull it out.

164
00:16:53,408 --> 00:16:55,037
- Slowly. Slowly, slowly.
- Duke.

165
00:16:55,111 --> 00:16:56,876
All right, go ahead.

166
