945
01:13:44,430 --> 01:13:47,095
- From a pay phone?
- Not from anywhere.

946
01:13:47,872 --> 01:13:50,341
Why? What's going on?

947
01:13:52,014 --> 01:13:54,951
- Nigel Bingham.
- Nigel Bingham?

948
01:13:55,019 --> 01:13:58,047
- You were together in Athens.
- He was my station chief.

949
01:13:58,158 --> 01:14:00,788
- You still on good terms?
- Great. Why?

950
01:14:01,297 --> 01:14:03,701
Equikrom, the special unit, they're hiring.

951
01:14:03,802 --> 01:14:07,242
Duke needs a field agent.
I figured out a way to get you in.

952
01:14:07,342 --> 01:14:09,836
It's happening, Ray. It's war.

953
01:14:09,914 --> 01:14:13,512
- What do you mean, war?
- I mean like a total corporate death match.

954
01:14:13,588 --> 01:14:16,685
We're on. B&R is about to make a move.

955
01:14:16,761 --> 01:14:20,164
- What kind of move?
- Some new product. Something big.

956
01:14:20,234 --> 01:14:22,000
What do you mean, "big"?

957
01:14:22,072 --> 01:14:26,409
Big, big like we've had four top-down
tech sweeps in the last two weeks.

958
01:14:26,512 --> 01:14:30,748
Big like three days ago
we started auditing passwords hourly.

959
01:14:31,189 --> 01:14:33,524
This morning I got a message from Duke.

960
01:14:33,594 --> 01:14:36,463
