Okay, so don't turn around,
but she just came in.

1018
01:18:19,201 --> 01:18:22,195
- We're cool though, right? She see us?
- Oh, yeah.

1019
01:18:22,306 --> 01:18:25,005
- I look natural, right?
- Super natural.

1020
01:18:29,520 --> 01:18:31,319
Who picked this place?

1021
01:18:31,391 --> 01:18:34,386
- You have a problem?
- It's a little bright.

1022
01:18:35,364 --> 01:18:38,359
- So this gentleman here is...
- I know who he is.

1023
01:18:38,471 --> 01:18:41,807
You do? Even with the hat?

1024
01:18:42,680 --> 01:18:44,877
She's a trained professional.

1025
01:18:44,984 --> 01:18:47,421
Yeah, yeah, I can see that.

1026
01:18:48,190 --> 01:18:50,387
I can definitely...

1027
01:18:51,329 --> 01:18:53,664
Would you...
You know what, we got beers here.

1028
01:18:53,734 --> 01:18:55,168
- Would you care for something?
- She's fine.

1029
01:18:55,238 --> 01:18:58,404
- I'm starving.
- Well, hell, then we should feed you.

1030
01:18:58,511 --> 01:19:00,605
I'd love some pizza.
Do you think they have pizza?

1031
01:19:00,715 --> 01:19:02,412
I'll just bet that they do, yeah.

1032
01:19:02,519 --> 01:19:04,045
- Or even frozen pizza.
- Okay.

1033
01:19:04,122 --> 01:19:06,684
- I don't think so.
- Why don't you go take a look-see?

1034
01:19:06,760 --> 01:19:08,229
You'd smell it if they did.

1035
01:19:08,296 --> 01:19:12,896
I don't give a damn if you have to go
to Sicily, get the lady some pizza!

1036
01:19:15,912 --> 01:19:17,814
Any particular topping you'd like?

1037
01:19:17,916 --> 01:19:19,384
Surprise me.

1038
01:19:24,295 --> 01:19:25,456
Pepperoni.

1039
01:19:26,666 --> 01:19:28,931
Super Cheese-a-peno.

1040
01:19:29,572 --> 01:19:31,404
Mushroom.

1041
01:19:32,176 --> 01:19:33,975
Mushroom and onion.

1042
01:19:35,416 --> 01:19:37,146
Plain.

1043
01:19:37,854 --> 01:19:39,824
- Hawaiian.
- Plain.

1044
01:19:44,333 --> 01:19:47,795
- Do you like it hot or...
- Yeah, hot. Very hot.

1045
01:19:48,876 --> 01:19:50,435
Extremely hot.

1046
01:19:54,654 --> 01:19:56,555
You want something to drink?

1047
01:19:56,658 --> 01:19:58,685
Yeah, sure, whatever.

1048
01:20:06,143 --> 01:20:08,704
What's going on? What just happened?

1049
01:20:09,181 --> 01:20:10,649
You...

1050
01:20:11,353 --> 01:20:13,185
You gotta get Duke. You gotta get Duke.

1051
01:20:13,256 --> 01:20:16,717
And you've gotta tell him
to get me a secure line

1052
01:20:16,829 --> 01:20:18,229
because he's gotta call me right away.

1053
01:20:18,332 --> 01:20:20,827
- What did she say?
- Secure line.

1054
01:20:20,904 --> 01:20:23,534
Do you understand me?
And only if he is sure.

1055
01:20:23,609 --> 01:20:26,081
I gotta get on the plane,
and he's gotta call me,

1056
01:20:26,181 --> 01:20:28,583
but it has gotta be safe.

1057
01:20:43,882 --> 01:20:46,752
Yeah, it's me. I need Duke. Now.

1058
01:20:48,492 --> 01:20:50,984
Yeah. Well, tell him to hurry up.

1059
01:22:15,094 --> 01:22:16,893
What are you doing?

1060
01:22:17,599 --> 01:22:18,725
Me?

1061
01:22:18,801 --> 01:22:21,500
- How did you get here so fast?
- Not fast enough though, right?

1062
01:22:21,606 --> 01:22:23,667
- You're leaving?
- I didn't think you were coming.

1063
01:22:23,778 --> 01:22:24,972
I left the signal, didn't I?

1064
01:22:25,079 --> 01:22:27,175
You also took your passports
and the travel money.

1065
01:22:27,284 --> 01:22:29,186
Half the money. My half.

1066
01:22:29,288 --> 01:22:32,658
We took a vow. No one touches
the mayday pouch until it's time to bail.

1067
01:22:32,761 --> 01:22:33,820
I trusted you.

1068
01:22:33,930 --> 01:22:36,630
Which explains
why you were in there checking it.

1069
01:22:36,703 --> 01:22:38,296
- When did you do this?
- When?

1070
01:22:38,372 --> 01:22:43,279
About five or six hours after I got done
with Barbara Bofferd from B&R Travel.

1071
01:22:44,051 --> 01:22:45,645
You're kidding.

1072
01:22:46,689 --> 01:22:49,182
- That's what this is about?
- That?

1073
01:22:49,728 --> 01:22:52,164
We're in play, for Christ's sake.
We don't have time for this.

1074
01:22:52,234 --> 01:22:54,533
Why? Is it a long explanation?

1075
01:22:55,239 --> 01:22:56,572
Walk.

1076
01:22:57,076 --> 01:22:58,636
What the hell did you just tell Garsik?

1077
01:22:58,712 --> 01:23:00,409
- You're unbelievable.
- What's the secret?

1078
01:23:00,515 --> 01:23:03,009
- You screwed her!
- Yeah. For us. For the project.

1079
01:23:03,087 --> 01:23:06,253
- I can't believe you screwed her!
- It was an assignment. It was nothing.

1080
01:23:06,360 --> 01:23:07,694
Well, you should see the pictures.

1081
01:23:07,764 --> 01:23:09,595
Well, you're the last person
I need to explain this to.

1082
01:23:09,699 --> 01:23:11,328
The only difference
between this and our first date

1083
01:23:11,404 --> 01:23:13,600
is that no one was drugged into a coma
and left for dead.

1084
01:23:13,707 --> 01:23:16,407
Left for dead? You were asleep in bed
with a smile on your face!

1085
01:23:16,514 --> 01:23:18,574
- Yeah, for 18 bloody hours!
- See, there it is.

1086
01:23:18,685 --> 01:23:20,847
- You can't get past Dubai, can you?
- What's the product, Claire?

1087
01:23:20,921 --> 01:23:22,891
- You say that you can, but you can't.
- What is the product?

1088
01:23:22,960 --> 01:23:26,421
All right, you know what,
I did come back here to clear out my stuff.

1089
01:23:26,533 --> 01:23:28,765
All right, I was gone. I was ready to bail.

1090
01:23:28,872 --> 01:23:31,434
I got the pouch out, I'm halfway there,
and I suddenly realize,

1091
01:23:31,542 --> 01:23:35,779
"Oh, my God! What are you doing?
This is good. This could work. It's payback.

1092
01:23:35,885 --> 01:23:39,449
"We take Dubai, the travel tramp, call it even,
move on, never mention it again."

1093
01:23:39,559 --> 01:23:41,118
So, there I am, I'm loading it all back in,

1094
01:23:41,228 --> 01:23:42,662
I'm putting everything away,
like it never happened,

1095
01:23:42,765 --> 01:23:46,225
and I suddenly realize
there's something missing.

1096
01:23:46,305 --> 01:23:48,640
- Where's Ray's Canadian passport?
- Okay, slow down.

1097
01:23:48,743 --> 01:23:50,645
Which I know for a fact
is supposed to be in there

1098
01:23:50,747 --> 01:23:52,979
because I'm the one
who taped the whole thing together!

1099
01:23:53,086 --> 01:23:55,420
Yes, okay?
Yes, I took the Canadian passport.

1100
01:23:55,489 --> 01:23:57,789
One passport. Why?
Because I was paranoid.

1101
01:23:57,860 --> 01:24:00,127
All this probing and testing
and not trusting me, it gets to you.

1102
01:24:00,199 --> 01:24:02,135
I thought, what's the harm
in having one little parachute

1103
01:24:02,203 --> 01:24:03,364
in case the plane goes down?

1104
01:24:03,472 --> 01:24:05,966
I wanted a hole card. That's it.
That's all it was.

1105
01:24:06,043 --> 01:24:09,814
And the travel lady, did I have to go
that far? Maybe not. But it worked.

1106
01:24:09,885 --> 01:24:13,345
And you know what, that's my cover.
That's always been my cover.

1107
01:24:13,457 --> 01:24:17,023
I'm a mess. I'm a horndog. I'm a slob.
But that's my edge.

1108
01:24:17,132 --> 01:24:18,725
I mean, we're here trying to run a triple game

1109
01:24:18,835 --> 01:24:21,305
on some very smart
and very motivated players.

1110
01:24:21,373 --> 01:24:23,640
What do you want me to do,
play with one hand behind my back?

1111
01:24:23,712 --> 01:24:26,376
It wasn't your hand I was talking about.

1112
01:24:26,484 --> 01:24:28,750
You know what? Get over it.

1113
01:24:29,155 --> 01:24:31,216
You know what? I'm there.

1114
01:24:33,564 --> 01:24:34,725
So what are you saying?

1115
01:24:34,833 --> 01:24:37,895
Same split, new rules.
You keep your parachute. I'll keep mine.

1116
01:24:38,006 --> 01:24:40,170
- You're that jealous?
- No, I'm that focused.

1117
01:24:40,243 --> 01:24:42,007
I've got two years invested in this,

1118
01:24:42,079 --> 01:24:45,917
and the last thing I'm gonna do is let some
stupid, immature personal baggage

1119
01:24:46,021 --> 01:24:48,515
compromise an otherwise
successful operation.

1120
01:24:48,594 --> 01:24:50,587
- So we're strictly business now.
- Deal with it.

1121
01:24:50,698 --> 01:24:53,260
Well, it might help if I knew
what kind of business we were in.

1122
01:24:53,368 --> 01:24:56,238
Hair. They can grow hair.

1123
01:24:56,742 --> 01:24:58,439
Where it belongs.

1124
01:24:59,582 --> 01:25:00,708
You mean what? Like...

1125
01:25:00,783 --> 01:25:04,724
Like, from now on, Ronnie Partiz
will be the patron saint to all bald men.

1126
01:25:04,792 --> 01:25:08,162
- Except there won't be any bald men.
- A cure for baldness?

1127
01:25:08,265 --> 01:25:13,675
Burkett & Randle Wash and Grow Shampoo,
enriched with activated Partizonol.

1128
01:25:15,814 --> 01:25:18,444
- Hair? That's like...
- It's huge.

1129
01:25:19,119 --> 01:25:22,524
Huge? It's beyond huge.
It makes huge look bloody microscopic.

1130
01:25:22,627 --> 01:25:26,362
Do you have any idea what this is worth?
I mean, hair.

1131
01:25:28,337 --> 01:25:31,502
To grow hair, to own that,
that's the all-time Holy Grail.

1132
01:25:31,610 --> 01:25:33,807
No wonder they've been so crazy.

1133
01:25:33,881 --> 01:25:36,478
I mean, we're sitting here
on a cure for baldness

1134
01:25:36,554 --> 01:25:39,287
and you're getting worked up
about some meaningless incident.

1135
01:25:39,359 --> 01:25:43,628
- We don't have it.
- We don't? But it's a formula though, right?

1136
01:25:44,168 --> 01:25:47,630
It has to be. It has to be a formula
with a patent application.

1137
01:25:47,708 --> 01:25:50,235
- So who's got it? Where is it?
- I don't know.

1138
01:25:50,346 --> 01:25:52,043
If you did,
you'd be sharing that, though, right?

1139
01:25:52,150 --> 01:25:55,453
If I were holding out on you,
what would I be doing here now?

1140
01:25:55,524 --> 01:25:57,186
How about pretending
to be pissed off and jealous

1141
01:25:57,293 --> 01:25:59,059
just to keep me from thinking
what was really going on.

